title: How Death Valley Got Its Name
The Little Dressmaker of Bodie
description: In the small High Sierras town of Bodie, a modest seamstress has settled down unnoticed. But what the townspeople do not know is that this woman used to be acclaimed as Tiger Lil, the star singer of Virginia City, during the gold rush days. Her life was turned upside down when her lover dumped her. Devastated, Tiger Lil gave up singing and after taking on a new name, took refuge among them...

title: The Lady with the Blue Silk Umbrella
Sego Lilies
description: A young woman has trouble adjusting to the rough prairie after her Mormon husband is called to settle a new "Zion" away from Salt Lake City. The longer she stays there, the more she wants to leave until she finally has to take desperate measures to get what she thinks she truly wants.

title: Little Washington
description: The tale of a society belle of Washington, D.C. who is transplanted to Carson City, Nevada, then known as "Little Washington".

title: Dear Teacher
description: New schoolteacher arrives, keeps unruly students in line with her sweet demeanor and sharpshooting skills. One vindictive female student and some town busybodies try to get her run out of town.

title: Eleven Thousand Miners Can't Be Wrong
To Big Charlie from Little Charlie
Death Valley Scotty
description: This episode re-creates the record-breaking run of the "Scott Special," a passenger train of the Atchison, Topeka and Santa Fe Railway commissioned by Walter E. Scott in 1905. Santa Fe #1010, one of the original steam locomotives used on the special, was reconditioned especially for filming.

title: Gold Is Where You Find It
The Man Who'd Bet on Anything
Bill Bottle's Birthday
description: Bill sells his gold claim to a business syndicate for $100,000. Now loaded, he invites his long-lost relatives to town for an elaborate family reunion. All the arriving guests claim to be Bottles, but are really grifters hoping to get their hands on some of his fortune. The phonies learn a lesson from Bill who treats all of them as warmly as if they were legitimate family.

title: The Longest Beard in the World
The Man Who Was Never Licked
The Girl Who Walked with a Giant
A Piano Goes West
description: A player piano in a saloon plays a particular melody that evokes a somewhat strange reaction from a woman and gives a clue to a man's disappearance.

title: Sailor on a Horse
description: A US Navy officer is assigned to chart the Missouri River, but he runs into some unexpected hostility from a bull-headed army officer.

title: The Newspaper That Went to Jail
Tribal Justice
description: The son of an Indian chief accused of the murder of a fellow tribesman faces trial.

title: One Man Tank
description: Prospector "Dutch" Charley Koehn (

title: The Great Lounsberry Scoop
description: Colonel Lounsberry is selected by General Custer to be the only newspaperman to travel with the troops leaving on a campaign against the Sioux.

title: Alias James Stuart
description: Jansen's store is robbed by James Stuart and Jansen is knifed. A man is arrested who bears an uncanny resemblance to James Stuart, but the arrestee claims to be Thomas Burdue. Jansen dies before he can identify the robber, and the remainder of this story centers on the trial of the arrestee. Is this man James Stuart or is he Thomas Burdue? Only Mrs. James Stuart knows.

title: The Hat That Won the West
The Private Mint of Clark, Gruber and Company
A Gun Is Not a Gentleman
The Lion of Idaho
description: William E. Borah, later to become a U.S. Senator from Idaho, is portrayed here as a young attorney defending a woman on a murder charge in Nampa, ID.

title: Three Minutes to Eternity
description: The Dalton Brothers try to rob two banks at the same time.

title: The Red Ghost of Eagle Creek
See the Elephant and Hear the Owl
Raid on the San Francisco Mint
The Battle of San Francisco Bay
The Wild West's Biggest Train Holdup
The Fastest Nun in the West
The Fight San Francisco Will Never Forget
Lady of the Plains
description: A gambler (DeForest Kelley) tries to win the heart of a society belle.

title: The Day All Marriages Were Cancelled
The Kid from Hell's Kitchen
description: Billy the Kid sets out to avenge the death of a friend.

title: The Jolly Roger and Wells Fargo
The Man Who Didn't Want Gold
The Day They Stole the Salamander
The Girl Who Walked the West
The Great Diamond Mines
description: A prospector and his partner try to con a banker.

title: Count Me In, Count Me Out
Green Is the Color of Gold
Out of the Valley of Death
The Gold Mine on Main Street
The Thirty Calibre Town
description: The story of how the Winchester repeating rifle helped to bring law and order to a north Idaho town. Filmed on location in Winchester, Idaho.

title: The Other Side of the Mountain
The Pieces of the Puzzle
description: "The Baron of Arizona," James Reavis, files a claim against the government.

title: The Secret of the Black Prince
A Mule... Like the Army's Mule
description: Sandy King, the youngest member of an outlaw gang, is wounded. The gang captures army lieutenant Jason Beal, but agree to free him on condition that he take King for treatment by army doctors, without arrest. When the healed King returns to his gang, he provides them information for another robbery: stealing a group of horses from the army.

title: Biscuits and Billy, the Kid
description: A blue eyed goat named Billy and a mother's ability to bake biscuits help family members traveling by wagon from Utah to California when they are abandoned by their guide.

title: The Great Pinto Bean Gold Hunt
The King of the Uvalde Road
The Biggest Little Post Office in the World
The Man Who Planted Gold in California
